A car is understood to have struck a barrier on the M8 at Harthill, causing delays. Delays after M8 crash near Glasgow A car is understood to have struck a barrier on the M8 at Harthill, causing delays.Police Scotland said the accident was reported at 9.40am, between junctions 5 and 6 westbound.A spokeswoman said a car is believed to have struck the barrier.Traffic Scotland said three vehicles are involved and the carriageway is strewn with debris.Drivers are warned to expect delays around junction 5, which is partially blocked.It is not known if anyone is injured. A spokeswoman for the Scottish Ambulance Service confirmed they are on scene but could not give details of any injuries. 